==English==

===Etymology===
From {{prefix|re|purpose}}.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|repurpos|es}}

# To re-use for a different purpose, on a long-term basis
#: ''The meadows were '''repurposed''' as playing fields.''
# To alter to make more suited for a different purpose
#: ''The church was '''repurposed''' as a nightclub by lighting changes and removing the pews.''

